    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can set this setting here.</p>\n\n<p>In <strong>IDEA 14</strong>+ the sequence is:  </p>\n\n<p><code>Settings</code> > <code>Editor</code> > <code>Code Style</code> > <code>Java</code> > <code>Imports</code> > <code>Class count to use import with '*'</code></p>\n\n<p>In older version of IDEA:</p>\n\n<p><code>Settings</code> -> <code>Java</code> -> <code>Code Style</code> -> <code>Imports</code> -> <code>Class count to use import with '*'</code></p>\n\n<p>The feature can not be disabled. You need to set it to a high value, e.g. 99.</p>\n\n<p>In 2016.1.1 version\nYou should also remove the lines under <code>Packages to Use Import with '*'</code>, \ne.g. <code>import javax.*;</code></p>\n"
  }, {
